                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.796 Avianca/77: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-23T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 23, 1940—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—12:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. My telegram No. 48, to safety measures set forth by the President, there
                    should be added his statement that the Government will also be guided throughout
                    on defense measures by the advice of the United States Military Aviation
                    Mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
